data.title: Official Music Videos Archives
data.text:
Traci Braxton is between shooting several reality shows and has been busy in the studio. We’re so excited to hear new music from the singer because it’s been quite some time since we’ve heard Traci release a solo project. No worries because Traci is back with something new and we absolutely love her new single. […]

Get ready to dance! DJ Cassidy and R. Kelly join forces for feel good hit, “Make the World Go Round” just in time for the summer. Watch the video as they dance and sing on a groovy subway ride through the city. Let us know what you think about this jam in the poll below! RELATED: R. Kelly’s Child Takes To Social Media […]

The reviews of Michael Jackson‘s latest project Xscape are in and are pretty impressive. Timbaland and Jerome “J-Roc” Harmon, Stargate, Rodney Jerkins and John McClain and L.A. Reid all collaborated on bringing this project to life. Check out the first video from the album featuring Justin Timberlake. What are your thoughts? WIN A FREE DOWNLOAD […]

New Video features 10 minutes of an six hour performance at Chelsea Pace Gallery in NYC. The video originally premiered following Jay Z’s appearance on Real Time With Bill Maher. See how many celebrity faces you can identify in this amazing video.

Tamar Braxton’s long waited Love and War video, the single off of her upcoming album of the same name is shot entirely in Black and White. Love and War soared to the top of Itunes chart the day after it debuted which delighted and amazed Tamar.

Our Holiday Concert Series artist Chrisette Michele has just dropped the visual for new single “Charades” from her Audrey Hepburn project. The video is directed by Atlanta photographer Derek Blanks. Watch the video below. Chrisette will be performing this Saturday November 17th at Rams Head Live get your tickets now!

Alicia Keys is a wonder woman in her newest video, ‘Girl On Fire’ which shows her taking on the daily responsibility of most women; taking care of children, family, cooking, cleaning and the whole nine while still managing to look absolutely stunning. She reminds us why most women are girls on fire.

Now that Nikki Minaj has been officially named one of the judges for American Idol her influences and brand will be bigger than ever. But is Nikki Minaj a role model for the families that are drawn to the innocence of American Idol? Baltimore’s Watoto From The Nile don’t think so. The young starlets are back with […]

Today would have been Michael Jackson 54th Birthday and all day on Magic 95.9 we are playing nothing but MJ music. What’s your favorite song? I have three Butterflies, PYT and Remember The Time. Which is my absolute favorite. I remember seeing the video and learning every dance step. The visuals, the actors, the dancers and Michael […]

Usher has another hit on his hands with “Dive,” and you’re going to love the visuals of this sexy music video. Take a look at Usher loving on supermodel Chanel Iman, and make sure to add his latest album “Looking 4 Myself” to your collection by clicking here.

Erykah Badu‘s the eclectic, soulful singer has just released a new music video collaboration with The Flaming Lips. “The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face” is a classic by Roberta Flack that shows Erykah naked in a bathtube. While Erykah Badu does show some skin, it’s her sister who shows it all. The close-up shots of naked body […]
